From: Kyle Petryszak <kyle@petryszak.com>
Date: Wed, 13 May 2026 00:00:00 -0500
Subject: [PATCH] phy: rockchip-naneng-combphy: PCIe receiver detection errata

Apply force_det_out after PHY reset deassert to match vendor kernel
sequencing. The register write in rk3588_combphy_cfg() was being
cleared by the subsequent reset_control_deassert().

Signed-off-by: Kyle Petryszak <kyle@petryszak.com>
---
 drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-naneng-combphy.c | 6 ++++++
 1 file changed, 6 insertions(+)

diff --git a/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-naneng-combphy.c b/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-naneng-combphy.c
index 5b0b3fc8571d..8e0eb52a1edc 100644
--- a/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-naneng-combphy.c
+++ b/drivers/phy/rockchip/phy-rockchip-naneng-combphy.c
@@ -285,6 +285,12 @@ static int rockchip_combphy_init(struct phy *phy)
 	if (ret)
 		goto err_clk;
 
+	/* PCIe receiver detection errata workaround (force_det_out).
+	 * Must be after reset_control_deassert() or the reset clears it.
+	 */
+	if (priv->type == PHY_TYPE_PCIE)
+		rockchip_combphy_updatel(priv, GENMASK(5, 5), BIT(5), 0x19 << 2);
+
 	if (priv->type == PHY_TYPE_USB3) {
 		ret = readx_poll_timeout_atomic(rockchip_combphy_is_ready,
 						priv, val,
-- 
2.39.5
